v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

31// Adds Arm64-specific methods to convert InstructionOperands.
32class Arm64OperandConverter final : public InstructionOperandConverter {
33 public:
34 Arm64OperandConverter(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
35 : InstructionOperandConverter(gen, instr) {}
36
37 DoubleRegister InputFloat32Register(size_t index) {
38 return InputDoubleRegister(index).S();
39 }
40
41 DoubleRegister InputFloat64Register(size_t index) {
42 return InputDoubleRegister(index);
43 }
44
45 DoubleRegister InputSimd128Register(size_t index) {
46 return InputDoubleRegister(index).Q();
47 }
48
49 CPURegister InputFloat32OrZeroRegister(size_t index) {
50 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
51 DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int32_t>(InputFloat32(index)));
52 return wzr;
53 }
54 DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsFPRegister());
55 return InputDoubleRegister(index).S();
56 }
57
58 DoubleRegister InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(size_t index) {
59 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
60 DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int32_t>(InputFloat32(index)));
61 return fp_zero.S();
62 }
63 DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsFPRegister());
64 return InputDoubleRegister(index).S();
65 }
66
67 CPURegister InputFloat64OrZeroRegister(size_t index) {
68 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
69 DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int64_t>(InputDouble(index)));
70 return xzr;
71 }
72 DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsDoubleRegister());
73 return InputDoubleRegister(index);
74 }
75
76 DoubleRegister InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(size_t index) {
77 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
78 DCHECK_EQ(0, base::bit_cast<int64_t>(InputDouble(index)));
79 return fp_zero;
80 }
81 DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsDoubleRegister());
82 return InputDoubleRegister(index);
83 }
84
85 size_t OutputCount() { return instr_->OutputCount(); }
86
87 DoubleRegister OutputFloat32Register(size_t index = 0) {
88 return OutputDoubleRegister(index).S();
89 }
90
91 DoubleRegister OutputFloat64Register(size_t index = 0) {
92 return OutputDoubleRegister(index);
93 }
94
95 DoubleRegister OutputSimd128Register() { return OutputDoubleRegister().Q(); }
96
97 Register InputRegister32(size_t index) {
98 return ToRegister(instr_->InputAt(index)).W();
99 }
100
101 Register InputOrZeroRegister32(size_t index) {
102 DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsRegister() ||
103 (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate() && (InputInt32(index) == 0)));
104 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
105 return wzr;
106 }
107 return InputRegister32(index);
108 }
109
110 Register InputRegister64(size_t index) { return InputRegister(index); }
111
112 Register InputOrZeroRegister64(size_t index) {
113 DCHECK(instr_->InputAt(index)->IsRegister() ||
114 (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate() && (InputInt64(index) == 0)));
115 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
116 return xzr;
117 }
118 return InputRegister64(index);
119 }
120
121 Operand InputOperand(size_t index) {
122 return ToOperand(instr_->InputAt(index));
123 }
124
125 Operand InputOperand64(size_t index) { return InputOperand(index); }
126
127 Operand InputOperand32(size_t index) {
128 return ToOperand32(instr_->InputAt(index));
129 }
130
131 Register OutputRegister64(size_t index = 0) { return OutputRegister(index); }
132
133 Register OutputRegister32(size_t index = 0) {
134 return OutputRegister(index).W();
135 }
136
137 Register TempRegister32(size_t index) {
138 return ToRegister(instr_->TempAt(index)).W();
139 }
140
141 Operand InputOperand2_32(size_t index) {
142 switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
143 case kMode_None:
144 return InputOperand32(index);
145 case kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I:
146 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), LSL, InputInt5(index + 1));
147 case kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I:
148 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), LSR, InputInt5(index + 1));
149 case kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I:
150 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), ASR, InputInt5(index + 1));
151 case kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I:
152 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), ROR, InputInt5(index + 1));
153 case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB:
154 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), UXTB);
155 case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH:
156 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), UXTH);
157 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB:
158 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), SXTB);
159 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH:
160 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), SXTH);
161 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW:
162 return Operand(InputRegister32(index), SXTW);
163 case kMode_MRI:
164 case kMode_MRR:
165 case kMode_Root:
166 break;
167 }
168 UNREACHABLE();
169 }
170
171 Operand InputOperand2_64(size_t index) {
172 switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
173 case kMode_None:
174 return InputOperand64(index);
175 case kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I:
176 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), LSL, InputInt6(index + 1));
177 case kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I:
178 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), LSR, InputInt6(index + 1));
179 case kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I:
180 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), ASR, InputInt6(index + 1));
181 case kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I:
182 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), ROR, InputInt6(index + 1));
183 case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB:
184 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), UXTB);
185 case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH:
186 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), UXTH);
187 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB:
188 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), SXTB);
189 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH:
190 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), SXTH);
191 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW:
192 return Operand(InputRegister64(index), SXTW);
193 case kMode_MRI:
194 case kMode_MRR:
195 case kMode_Root:
196 break;
197 }
198 UNREACHABLE();
199 }
200
201 MemOperand MemoryOperand(size_t index = 0) {
202 switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
203 case kMode_None:
204 case kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I:
205 case kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I:
206 case kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I:
207 case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB:
208 case kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH:
209 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB:
210 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH:
211 case kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW:
212 break;
213 case kMode_Root:
214 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, InputInt64(index));
215 case kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I:
216 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1),
217 LSL, InputInt32(index + 2));
218 case kMode_MRI:
219 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputInt32(index + 1));
220 case kMode_MRR:
221 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1));
222 }
223 UNREACHABLE();
224 }
225
226 Operand ToOperand(InstructionOperand* op) {
227 if (op->IsRegister()) {
228 return Operand(ToRegister(op));
229 }
230 return ToImmediate(op);
231 }
232
233 Operand ToOperand32(InstructionOperand* op) {
234 if (op->IsRegister()) {
235 return Operand(ToRegister(op).W());
236 }
237 return ToImmediate(op);
238 }
239
240 Operand ToImmediate(InstructionOperand* operand) {
241 Constant constant = ToConstant(operand);
242 switch (constant.type()) {
243 case Constant::kInt32:
244 return Operand(constant.ToInt32(), constant.rmode());
245 case Constant::kInt64:
246 return Operand(constant.ToInt64(), constant.rmode());
247 case Constant::kFloat32:
248 return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat32());
249 case Constant::kFloat64:
250 return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat64().value());
251 case Constant::kExternalReference:
252 return Operand(constant.ToExternalReference());
253 case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject: {
254 RootIndex root_index;
255 if (gen_->isolate()->roots_table().IsRootHandle(constant.ToHeapObject(),
256 &root_index)) {
257 CHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
258 CHECK(V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL || !gen_->isolate()->bootstrapper());
259 Tagged_t ptr =
260 MacroAssemblerBase::ReadOnlyRootPtr(root_index, gen_->isolate());
261 CHECK(Assembler::IsImmAddSub(ptr));
262 return Immediate(ptr);
263 }
264
265 return Operand(constant.ToHeapObject());
266 }
267 case Constant::kHeapObject:
268 return Operand(constant.ToHeapObject());
269 case Constant::kRpoNumber:
270 UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(dcarney): RPO immediates on arm64.
271 }
272 UNREACHABLE();
273 }
274
275 MemOperand ToMemOperand(InstructionOperand* op, MacroAssembler* masm) const {
276 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(op);
277 DCHECK(op->IsStackSlot() || op->IsFPStackSlot());
278 return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index(), masm);
279 }
280
281 MemOperand SlotToMemOperand(int slot, MacroAssembler* masm) const {
282 FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(slot);
283 if (offset.from_frame_pointer()) {
284 int from_sp = offset.offset() + frame_access_state()->GetSPToFPOffset();
285 // Convert FP-offsets to SP-offsets if it results in better code.
286 if (!frame_access_state()->FPRelativeOnly() &&
287 (Assembler::IsImmLSUnscaled(from_sp) ||
288 Assembler::IsImmLSScaled(from_sp, 3))) {
289 offset = FrameOffset::FromStackPointer(from_sp);
290 }
291 }
292 // Access below the stack pointer is not expected in arm64 and is actively
293 // prevented at run time in the simulator.
294 DCHECK_IMPLIES(offset.from_stack_pointer(), offset.offset() >= 0);
295 return MemOperand(offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp, offset.offset());
296 }
297};

301class OutOfLineRecordWrite final : public OutOfLineCode {
302 public:
303 OutOfLineRecordWrite(
304 CodeGenerator* gen, Register object, Operand offset, Register value,
305 RecordWriteMode mode, StubCallMode stub_mode,
306 UnwindingInfoWriter* unwinding_info_writer,
307 IndirectPointerTag indirect_pointer_tag = kIndirectPointerNullTag)
308 : OutOfLineCode(gen),
309 object_(object),
310 offset_(offset),
311 value_(value),
312 mode_(mode),
313#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
314 stub_mode_(stub_mode),
315#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
316 must_save_lr_(!gen->frame_access_state()->has_frame()),
317 unwinding_info_writer_(unwinding_info_writer),
318 zone_(gen->zone()),
319 indirect_pointer_tag_(indirect_pointer_tag) {
320 }
321
322 void Generate() final {
323 // When storing an indirect pointer, the value will always be a
324 // full/decompressed pointer.
325 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL &&
326 mode_ != RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
327 __ DecompressTagged(value_, value_);
328 }
329
330 // No need to check value page flags with the indirect pointer write barrier
331 // because the value is always an ExposedTrustedObject.
332 if (mode_ != RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
333 __ CheckPageFlag(value_, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
334 eq, exit());
335 }
336
337 SaveFPRegsMode const save_fp_mode = frame()->DidAllocateDoubleRegisters()
338 ? SaveFPRegsMode::kSave
339 : SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore;
340 if (must_save_lr_) {
341 // We need to save and restore lr if the frame was elided.
342 __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, padreg);
343 unwinding_info_writer_->MarkLinkRegisterOnTopOfStack(__ pc_offset(), sp);
344 }
345 if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsEphemeronKey) {
346 __ CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode);
347 } else if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
348 // We must have a valid indirect pointer tag here. Otherwise, we risk not
349 // invoking the correct write barrier, which may lead to subtle issues.
350 CHECK(IsValidIndirectPointerTag(indirect_pointer_tag_));
351 __ CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode,
352 indirect_pointer_tag_);
353#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
354 } else if (stub_mode_ == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
355 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
356 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched when the code
357 // is added to the native module and copied into wasm code space.
358 __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode,
359 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
360#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
361 } else {
362 __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, offset_, save_fp_mode);
363 }
364 if (must_save_lr_) {
365 __ Pop<MacroAssembler::kAuthLR>(padreg, lr);
366 unwinding_info_writer_->MarkPopLinkRegisterFromTopOfStack(__ pc_offset());
367 }
368 }
369
370 private:
371 Register const object_;
372 Operand const offset_;
373 Register const value_;
374 RecordWriteMode const mode_;
375#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
376 StubCallMode const stub_mode_;
377#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
378 bool must_save_lr_;
379 UnwindingInfoWriter* const unwinding_info_writer_;
380 Zone* zone_;
381 IndirectPointerTag indirect_pointer_tag_;
382};
383
384Condition FlagsConditionToCondition(FlagsCondition condition) {
385 switch (condition) {
386 case kEqual:
387 return eq;
388 case kNotEqual:
389 return ne;
390 case kSignedLessThan:
391 return lt;
392 case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
393 return ge;
394 case kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
395 return le;
396 case kSignedGreaterThan:
397 return gt;
398 case kUnsignedLessThan:
399 return lo;
400 case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
401 return hs;
402 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
403 return ls;
404 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
405 return hi;
406 case kFloatLessThanOrUnordered:
407 return lt;
408 case kFloatGreaterThanOrEqual:
409 return ge;
410 case kFloatLessThanOrEqual:
411 return ls;
412 case kFloatGreaterThanOrUnordered:
413 return hi;
414 case kFloatLessThan:
415 return lo;
416 case kFloatGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered:
417 return hs;
418 case kFloatLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered:
419 return le;
420 case kFloatGreaterThan:
421 return gt;
422 case kOverflow:
423 return vs;
424 case kNotOverflow:
425 return vc;
426 case kUnorderedEqual:
427 case kUnorderedNotEqual:
428 case kIsNaN:
429 case kIsNotNaN:
430 break;
431 case kPositiveOrZero:
432 return pl;
433 case kNegative:
434 return mi;
435 }
436 UNREACHABLE();
437}

439#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
440class WasmOutOfLineTrap : public OutOfLineCode {
441 public:
442 WasmOutOfLineTrap(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
443 : OutOfLineCode(gen), gen_(gen), instr_(instr) {}
444 void Generate() override {
445 Arm64OperandConverter i(gen_, instr_);
446 TrapId trap_id =
447 static_cast<TrapId>(i.InputInt32(instr_->InputCount() - 1));
448 GenerateCallToTrap(trap_id);
449 }
450
451 protected:
452 CodeGenerator* gen_;
453
454 void GenerateWithTrapId(TrapId trap_id) { GenerateCallToTrap(trap_id); }
455
456 private:
457 void GenerateCallToTrap(TrapId trap_id) {
458 gen_->AssembleSourcePosition(instr_);
459 __ Call(static_cast<Address>(trap_id), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
460 ReferenceMap* reference_map = gen_->zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(gen_->zone());
461 gen_->RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
462 __ AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromWasmTrap);
463 }
464
465 Instruction* instr_;
466};
467
468void RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(Zone* zone, CodeGenerator* codegen,
469 InstructionCode opcode, Instruction* instr,
470 int pc) {
471 const MemoryAccessMode access_mode = AccessModeField::decode(opcode);
472 if (access_mode == kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds ||
473 access_mode == kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference) {
474 codegen->RecordProtectedInstruction(pc);
475 }
476}
477#else
478void RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(Zone* zone, CodeGenerator* codegen,
479 InstructionCode opcode, Instruction* instr,
480 int pc) {
481 DCHECK_EQ(kMemoryAccessDirect, AccessModeField::decode(opcode));
482}
483#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

485// Handles unary ops that work for float (scalar), double (scalar), or NEON.
486template <typename Fn>
487void EmitFpOrNeonUnop(MacroAssembler* masm, Fn fn, Instruction* instr,
488 Arm64OperandConverter i, VectorFormat scalar,
489 VectorFormat vector) {
490 VectorFormat f = instr->InputAt(0)->IsSimd128Register() ? vector : scalar;
491
492 VRegister output = VRegister::Create(i.OutputDoubleRegister().code(), f);
493 VRegister input = VRegister::Create(i.InputDoubleRegister(0).code(), f);
494 (masm->*fn)(output, input);
495}

499#define ASSEMBLE_SHIFT(asm_instr, width) \
500 do { \
501 if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsRegister()) { \
502 __ asm_instr(i.OutputRegister##width(), i.InputRegister##width(0), \
503 i.InputRegister##width(1)); \
504 } else { \
505 uint32_t imm = \
506 static_cast<uint32_t>(i.InputOperand##width(1).ImmediateValue()); \
507 __ asm_instr(i.OutputRegister##width(), i.InputRegister##width(0), \
508 imm % (width)); \
509 } \
510 } while (0)
511
512#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_LOAD_INTEGER(asm_instr, reg) \
513 do { \
514 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
515 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
516 __ asm_instr(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
517 } while (0)
518
519#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_STORE_INTEGER(asm_instr, reg) \
520 do { \
521 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
522 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
523 __ asm_instr(i.Input##reg(2), i.TempRegister(0)); \
524 } while (0)
525
526#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(suffix, reg) \
527 do { \
528 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
529 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
530 CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
531 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
532 __ Swpal##suffix(i.Input##reg(2), i.Output##reg(), \
533 MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
534 } else { \
535 Label exchange; \
536 __ Bind(&exchange); \
537 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
538 __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
539 __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(1), i.Input##reg(2), \
540 i.TempRegister(0)); \
541 __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(1), &exchange); \
542 } \
543 } while (0)
544
545#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(suffix, ext, reg) \
546 do { \
547 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
548 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
549 DCHECK_EQ(i.OutputRegister(), i.InputRegister(2)); \
550 CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
551 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
552 __ Casal##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.Input##reg(3), \
553 MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
554 } else { \
555 Label compareExchange; \
556 Label exit; \
557 __ Bind(&compareExchange); \
558 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
559 __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
560 __ Cmp(i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2), ext)); \
561 __ B(ne, &exit); \
562 __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(1), i.Input##reg(3), \
563 i.TempRegister(0)); \
564 __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(1), &compareExchange); \
565 __ Bind(&exit); \
566 } \
567 } while (0)
568
569#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_SUB(suffix, reg) \
570 do { \
571 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
572 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
573 CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
574 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
575 Register scratch = temps.AcquireSameSizeAs(i.Input##reg(2)); \
576 __ Neg(scratch, i.Input##reg(2)); \
577 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
578 __ Ldaddal##suffix(scratch, i.Output##reg(), \
579 MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
580 } else { \
581 Label binop; \
582 __ Bind(&binop); \
583 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
584 __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
585 __ Sub(i.Temp##reg(1), i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2))); \
586 __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(2), i.Temp##reg(1), \
587 i.TempRegister(0)); \
588 __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(2), &binop); \
589 } \
590 } while (0)
591
592#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_AND(suffix, reg) \
593 do { \
594 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
595 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
596 CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
597 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
598 Register scratch = temps.AcquireSameSizeAs(i.Input##reg(2)); \
599 __ Mvn(scratch, i.Input##reg(2)); \
600 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
601 __ Ldclral##suffix(scratch, i.Output##reg(), \
602 MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
603 } else { \
604 Label binop; \
605 __ Bind(&binop); \
606 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
607 __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
608 __ And(i.Temp##reg(1), i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2))); \
609 __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(2), i.Temp##reg(1), \
610 i.TempRegister(0)); \
611 __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(2), &binop); \
612 } \
613 } while (0)
614
615#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(suffix, bin_instr, lse_instr, reg) \
616 do { \
617 __ Add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
618 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) { \
619 CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), LSE); \
620 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
621 __ lse_instr##suffix(i.Input##reg(2), i.Output##reg(), \
622 MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0))); \
623 } else { \
624 Label binop; \
625 __ Bind(&binop); \
626 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset()); \
627 __ ldaxr##suffix(i.Output##reg(), i.TempRegister(0)); \
628 __ bin_instr(i.Temp##reg(1), i.Output##reg(), Operand(i.Input##reg(2))); \
629 __ stlxr##suffix(i.TempRegister32(2), i.Temp##reg(1), \
630 i.TempRegister(0)); \
631 __ Cbnz(i.TempRegister32(2), &binop); \
632 } \
633 } while (0)
634
635#define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_BINOP(name) \
636 do { \
637 FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
638 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 2); \
639 } while (0)
640
641#define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(name) \
642 do { \
643 FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
644 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 1); \
645 } while (0)
646
647// If shift value is an immediate, we can call asm_imm, taking the shift value
648// modulo 2^width. Otherwise, emit code to perform the modulus operation, and
649// call asm_shl.
650#define ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_LEFT(asm_imm, width, format, asm_shl, gp) \
651 do { \
652 if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsImmediate()) { \
653 __ asm_imm(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
654 i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), i.InputInt##width(1)); \
655 } else { \
656 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
657 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireQ(); \
658 Register shift = temps.Acquire##gp(); \
659 constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1; \
660 __ And(shift, i.InputRegister32(1), mask); \
661 __ Dup(tmp.format(), shift); \
662 __ asm_shl(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
663 i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), tmp.format()); \
664 } \
665 } while (0)
666
667// If shift value is an immediate, we can call asm_imm, taking the shift value
668// modulo 2^width. Otherwise, emit code to perform the modulus operation, and
669// call asm_shl, passing in the negative shift value (treated as right shift).
670#define ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_RIGHT(asm_imm, width, format, asm_shl, gp) \
671 do { \
672 if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsImmediate()) { \
673 __ asm_imm(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
674 i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), i.InputInt##width(1)); \
675 } else { \
676 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm()); \
677 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireQ(); \
678 Register shift = temps.Acquire##gp(); \
679 constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1; \
680 __ And(shift, i.InputRegister32(1), mask); \
681 __ Dup(tmp.format(), shift); \
682 __ Neg(tmp.format(), tmp.format()); \
683 __ asm_shl(i.OutputSimd128Register().format(), \
684 i.InputSimd128Register(0).format(), tmp.format()); \
685 } \
686 } while (0)
687
688void CodeGenerator::AssembleDeconstructFrame() {
689 __ Mov(sp, fp);
690 __ Pop<MacroAssembler::kAuthLR>(fp, lr);
691
692 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkFrameDeconstructed(__ pc_offset());
693}
694
695void CodeGenerator::AssemblePrepareTailCall() {
696 if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
697 __ RestoreFPAndLR();
698 }
699 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToSP();
700}
701
702namespace {
703
704void AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(MacroAssembler* masm,
705 FrameAccessState* state,
706 int new_slot_above_sp,
707 bool allow_shrinkage = true) {
708 int current_sp_offset = state->GetSPToFPSlotCount() +
709 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountAboveFp;
710 int stack_slot_delta = new_slot_above_sp - current_sp_offset;
711 DCHECK_EQ(stack_slot_delta % 2, 0);
712 if (stack_slot_delta > 0) {
713 masm->Claim(stack_slot_delta);
714 state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
715 } else if (allow_shrinkage && stack_slot_delta < 0) {
716 masm->Drop(-stack_slot_delta);
717 state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
718 }
719}
720
721} // namespace
722
723void CodeGenerator::AssembleTailCallBeforeGap(Instruction* instr,
724 int first_unused_slot_offset) {
725 AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(masm(), frame_access_state(),
726 first_unused_slot_offset, false);
727}
728
729void CodeGenerator::AssembleTailCallAfterGap(Instruction* instr,
730 int first_unused_slot_offset) {
731 DCHECK_EQ(first_unused_slot_offset % 2, 0);
732 AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(masm(), frame_access_state(),
733 first_unused_slot_offset);
734 DCHECK(instr->IsTailCall());
735 InstructionOperandConverter g(this, instr);
736 int optional_padding_offset = g.InputInt32(instr->InputCount() - 2);
737 if (optional_padding_offset % 2) {
738 __ Poke(padreg, optional_padding_offset * kSystemPointerSize);
739 }
740}
741
742// Check that {kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister} is correct.
743void CodeGenerator::AssembleCodeStartRegisterCheck() {
744 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
745 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
746 __ ComputeCodeStartAddress(scratch);
747 __ cmp(scratch, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
748 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionCodeStart);
749}
750
751#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
752// Check that {kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister} is correct.
753void CodeGenerator::AssembleDispatchHandleRegisterCheck() {
754 DCHECK(linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->IsJSFunctionCall());
755
756 if (!V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL) return;
757
758 // We currently don't check this for JS builtins as those are sometimes
759 // called directly (e.g. from other builtins) and not through the dispatch
760 // table. This is fine as builtin functions don't use the dispatch handle,
761 // but we could enable this check in the future if we make sure to pass the
762 // kInvalidDispatchHandle whenever we do a direct call to a JS builtin.
763 if (Builtins::IsBuiltinId(info()->builtin())) {
764 return;
765 }
766
767 // For now, we only ensure that the register references a valid dispatch
768 // entry with the correct parameter count. In the future, we may also be able
769 // to check that the entry points back to this code.
770 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
771 Register actual_parameter_count = temps.AcquireX();
772 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
773 __ LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
774 actual_parameter_count, kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister, scratch);
775 __ Mov(scratch, parameter_count_);
776 __ cmp(actual_parameter_count, scratch);
777 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionDispatchHandle);
778}
779#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
780
781void CodeGenerator::BailoutIfDeoptimized() { __ BailoutIfDeoptimized(); }
782
783// Assembles an instruction after register allocation, producing machine code.
784CodeGenerator::CodeGenResult CodeGenerator::AssembleArchInstruction(
785 Instruction* instr) {
786 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
787 InstructionCode opcode = instr->opcode();
788 ArchOpcode arch_opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(opcode);
789 switch (arch_opcode) {
790 case kArchCallCodeObject: {
791 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
792 __ Call(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
793 } else {
794 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
795 CodeEntrypointTag tag =
796 i.InputCodeEntrypointTag(instr->CodeEnrypointTagInputIndex());
797 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
798 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
799 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
800 __ CallCodeObject(reg, tag);
801 }
802 RecordCallPosition(instr);
803 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
804 break;
805 }
806 case kArchCallBuiltinPointer: {
807 DCHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
808 Register builtin_index = i.InputRegister(0);
809 Register target =
810 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister)
811 ? kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister
812 : builtin_index;
813 __ CallBuiltinByIndex(builtin_index, target);
814 RecordCallPosition(instr);
815 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
816 break;
817 }
818#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
819 case kArchCallWasmFunction:
820 case kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect: {
821 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
822 DCHECK_EQ(arch_opcode, kArchCallWasmFunction);
823 Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
824 Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
825 __ Call(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
826 } else if (arch_opcode == kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect) {
827 __ CallWasmCodePointer(
828 i.InputRegister(0),
829 i.InputInt64(instr->WasmSignatureHashInputIndex()));
830 } else {
831 __ Call(i.InputRegister(0));
832 }
833 RecordCallPosition(instr);
834 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
835 break;
836 }
837 case kArchTailCallWasm:
838 case kArchTailCallWasmIndirect: {
839 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
840 DCHECK_EQ(arch_opcode, kArchTailCallWasm);
841 Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
842 Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
843 __ Jump(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
844 } else {
845 Register target = i.InputRegister(0);
846 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
847 temps.Exclude(x17);
848 __ Mov(x17, target);
849 if (arch_opcode == kArchTailCallWasmIndirect) {
850 __ CallWasmCodePointer(
851 x17, i.InputInt64(instr->WasmSignatureHashInputIndex()),
852 CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
853 } else {
854 __ Jump(x17);
855 }
856 }
857 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
858 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
859 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
860 break;
861 }
862#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
863 case kArchTailCallCodeObject: {
864 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
865 __ Jump(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
866 } else {
867 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
868 CodeEntrypointTag tag =
869 i.InputCodeEntrypointTag(instr->CodeEnrypointTagInputIndex());
870 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
871 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
872 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
873 __ JumpCodeObject(reg, tag);
874 }
875 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
876 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
877 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
878 break;
879 }
880 case kArchTailCallAddress: {
881 CHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
882 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
883 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
884 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
885 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
886 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
887 temps.Exclude(x17);
888 __ Mov(x17, reg);
889 __ Jump(x17);
890 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
891 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
892 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
893 break;
894 }
895 case kArchCallJSFunction: {
896 Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
897 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
898 // Check the function's context matches the context argument.
899 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
900 Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
901 __ LoadTaggedField(temp,
902 FieldMemOperand(func, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
903 __ cmp(cp, temp);
904 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionContext);
905 }
906 uint32_t num_arguments =
907 i.InputUint32(instr->JSCallArgumentCountInputIndex());
908 __ CallJSFunction(func, num_arguments);
909 RecordCallPosition(instr);
910 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
911 break;
912 }
913 case kArchPrepareCallCFunction:
914 // We don't need kArchPrepareCallCFunction on arm64 as the instruction
915 // selector has already performed a Claim to reserve space on the stack.
916 // Frame alignment is always 16 bytes, and the stack pointer is already
917 // 16-byte aligned, therefore we do not need to align the stack pointer
918 // by an unknown value, and it is safe to continue accessing the frame
919 // via the stack pointer.
920 UNREACHABLE();
921 case kArchSaveCallerRegisters: {
922 fp_mode_ =
923 static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode()));
924 DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
925 fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
926 // kReturnRegister0 should have been saved before entering the stub.
927 int bytes = __ PushCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
928 DCHECK(IsAligned(bytes, kSystemPointerSize));
929 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
930 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
931 DCHECK(!caller_registers_saved_);
932 caller_registers_saved_ = true;
933 break;
934 }
935 case kArchRestoreCallerRegisters: {
936 DCHECK(fp_mode_ ==
937 static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode())));
938 DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
939 fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
940 // Don't overwrite the returned value.
941 int bytes = __ PopCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
942 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-(bytes / kSystemPointerSize));
943 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
944 DCHECK(caller_registers_saved_);
945 caller_registers_saved_ = false;
946 break;
947 }
948 case kArchPrepareTailCall:
949 AssemblePrepareTailCall();
950 break;
951 case kArchCallCFunctionWithFrameState:
952 case kArchCallCFunction: {
953 int const num_gp_parameters = ParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
954 int const num_fp_parameters = FPParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
955 Label return_location;
956 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes;
957#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
958 if (linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
959 // Put the return address in a stack slot.
960 __ StoreReturnAddressInWasmExitFrame(&return_location);
961 set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo;
962 }
963#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
964 int pc_offset;
965 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
966 ExternalReference ref = i.InputExternalReference(0);
967 pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(ref, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
968 set_isolate_data_slots, &return_location);
969 } else {
970 Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
971 pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(func, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
972 set_isolate_data_slots, &return_location);
973 }
974 RecordSafepoint(instr->reference_map(), pc_offset);
975
976 bool const needs_frame_state =
977 (arch_opcode == kArchCallCFunctionWithFrameState);
978 if (needs_frame_state) {
979 RecordDeoptInfo(instr, pc_offset);
980 }
981
982 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
983 // Ideally, we should decrement SP delta to match the change of stack
984 // pointer in CallCFunction. However, for certain architectures (e.g.
985 // ARM), there may be more strict alignment requirement, causing old SP
986 // to be saved on the stack. In those cases, we can not calculate the SP
987 // delta statically.
988 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
989 if (caller_registers_saved_) {
990 // Need to re-sync SP delta introduced in kArchSaveCallerRegisters.
991 // Here, we assume the sequence to be:
992 // kArchSaveCallerRegisters;
993 // kArchCallCFunction;
994 // kArchRestoreCallerRegisters;
995 int bytes =
996 __ RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
997 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
998 }
999 break;
1000 }
1001 case kArchJmp:
1002 AssembleArchJump(i.InputRpo(0));
1003 break;
1004 case kArchTableSwitch:
1005 AssembleArchTableSwitch(instr);
1006 break;
1007 case kArchBinarySearchSwitch:
1008 AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitch(instr);
1009 break;
1010 case kArchAbortCSADcheck:
1011 DCHECK_EQ(i.InputRegister(0), x1);
1012 {
1013 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
1014 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
1015 FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
1016 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbortCSADcheck);
1017 }
1018 __ Debug("kArchAbortCSADcheck", 0, BREAK);
1019 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
1020 break;
1021 case kArchDebugBreak:
1022 __ DebugBreak();
1023 break;
1024 case kArchComment:
1025 __ RecordComment(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(i.InputInt64(0)));
1026 break;
1027 case kArchThrowTerminator:
1028 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
1029 break;
1030 case kArchNop:
1031 // don't emit code for nops.
1032 break;
1033 case kArchDeoptimize: {
1034 DeoptimizationExit* exit =
1035 BuildTranslation(instr, -1, 0, 0, OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore());
1036 __ B(exit->label());
1037 break;
1038 }
1039 case kArchRet:
1040 AssembleReturn(instr->InputAt(0));
1041 break;
1042 case kArchFramePointer:
1043 __ mov(i.OutputRegister(), fp);
1044 break;
1045 case kArchParentFramePointer:
1046 if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
1047 __ ldr(i.OutputRegister(), MemOperand(fp, 0));
1048 } else {
1049 __ mov(i.OutputRegister(), fp);
1050 }
1051 break;
1052#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1053 case kArchStackPointer:
1054 // The register allocator expects an allocatable register for the output,
1055 // we cannot use sp directly.
1056 __ mov(i.OutputRegister(), sp);
1057 break;
1058 case kArchSetStackPointer: {
1059 DCHECK(instr->InputAt(0)->IsRegister());
1060 if (masm()->options().enable_simulator_code) {
1061 __ RecordComment("-- Set simulator stack limit --");
1062 DCHECK(__ TmpList()->IncludesAliasOf(kSimulatorHltArgument));
1063 __ LoadStackLimit(kSimulatorHltArgument,
1064 StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
1065 __ hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
1066 }
1067 __ Mov(sp, i.InputRegister(0));
1068 break;
1069 }
1070#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1071 case kArchStackPointerGreaterThan: {
1072 // Potentially apply an offset to the current stack pointer before the
1073 // comparison to consider the size difference of an optimized frame versus
1074 // the contained unoptimized frames.
1075
1076 Register lhs_register = sp;
1077 uint32_t offset;
1078
1079 if (ShouldApplyOffsetToStackCheck(instr, &offset)) {
1080 lhs_register = i.TempRegister(0);
1081 __ Sub(lhs_register, sp, offset);
1082 }
1083
1084 constexpr size_t kValueIndex = 0;
1085 DCHECK(instr->InputAt(kValueIndex)->IsRegister());
1086 __ Cmp(lhs_register, i.InputRegister(kValueIndex));
1087 break;
1088 }
1089 case kArchStackCheckOffset:
1090 __ Move(i.OutputRegister(), Smi::FromInt(GetStackCheckOffset()));
1091 break;
1092 case kArchTruncateDoubleToI:
1093 __ TruncateDoubleToI(isolate(), zone(), i.OutputRegister(),
1094 i.InputDoubleRegister(0), DetermineStubCallMode(),
1095 frame_access_state()->has_frame()
1096 ? kLRHasBeenSaved
1097 : kLRHasNotBeenSaved);
1098
1099 break;
1100 case kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier: {
1101 RecordWriteMode mode = RecordWriteModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1102 // Indirect pointer writes must use a different opcode.
1103 DCHECK_NE(mode, RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer);
1104 AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1105 AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1106 Register object = i.InputRegister(0);
1107 Operand offset(0);
1108 if (addressing_mode == kMode_MRI) {
1109 offset = Operand(i.InputInt64(1));
1110 } else {
1111 DCHECK_EQ(addressing_mode, kMode_MRR);
1112 offset = Operand(i.InputRegister(1));
1113 }
1114 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
1115
1116 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1117 // Checking that |value| is not a cleared weakref: our write barrier
1118 // does not support that for now.
1119 __ cmp(value, Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));
1120 __ Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsCleared);
1121 }
1122
1123 auto ool = zone()->New<OutOfLineRecordWrite>(
1124 this, object, offset, value, mode, DetermineStubCallMode(),
1125 &unwinding_info_writer_);
1126 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset());
1127 __ StoreTaggedField(value, MemOperand(object, offset));
1128 if (mode > RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
1129 __ JumpIfSmi(value, ool->exit());
1130 }
1131 __ CheckPageFlag(object, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
1132 ne, ool->entry());
1133 __ Bind(ool->exit());
1134 break;
1135 }
1136 case kArchAtomicStoreWithWriteBarrier: {
1137 DCHECK_EQ(AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()), kMode_MRR);
1138 RecordWriteMode mode = RecordWriteModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1139 // Indirect pointer writes must use a different opcode.
1140 DCHECK_NE(mode, RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer);
1141 Register object = i.InputRegister(0);
1142 Register offset = i.InputRegister(1);
1143 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
1144 auto ool = zone()->New<OutOfLineRecordWrite>(
1145 this, object, offset, value, mode, DetermineStubCallMode(),
1146 &unwinding_info_writer_);
1147 __ AtomicStoreTaggedField(value, object, offset, i.TempRegister(0));
1148 // Skip the write barrier if the value is a Smi. However, this is only
1149 // valid if the value isn't an indirect pointer. Otherwise the value will
1150 // be a pointer table index, which will always look like a Smi (but
1151 // actually reference a pointer in the pointer table).
1152 if (mode > RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer) {
1153 __ JumpIfSmi(value, ool->exit());
1154 }
1155 __ CheckPageFlag(object, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
1156 ne, ool->entry());
1157 __ Bind(ool->exit());
1158 break;
1159 }
1160 case kArchStoreIndirectWithWriteBarrier: {
1161 RecordWriteMode mode = RecordWriteModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1162 DCHECK_EQ(mode, RecordWriteMode::kValueIsIndirectPointer);
1163 AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1164 AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1165 Register object = i.InputRegister(0);
1166 Operand offset(0);
1167 if (addressing_mode == kMode_MRI) {
1168 offset = Operand(i.InputInt64(1));
1169 } else {
1170 DCHECK_EQ(addressing_mode, kMode_MRR);
1171 offset = Operand(i.InputRegister(1));
1172 }
1173 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
1174 IndirectPointerTag tag = static_cast<IndirectPointerTag>(i.InputInt64(3));
1175 DCHECK(IsValidIndirectPointerTag(tag));
1176
1177 auto ool = zone()->New<OutOfLineRecordWrite>(
1178 this, object, offset, value, mode, DetermineStubCallMode(),
1179 &unwinding_info_writer_, tag);
1180 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset());
1181 __ StoreIndirectPointerField(value, MemOperand(object, offset));
1182 __ JumpIfMarking(ool->entry());
1183 __ Bind(ool->exit());
1184 break;
1185 }
1186 case kArchStackSlot: {
1187 FrameOffset offset =
1188 frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(i.InputInt32(0));
1189 Register base = offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp;
1190 __ Add(i.OutputRegister(0), base, Operand(offset.offset()));
1191 break;
1192 }
1193 case kIeee754Float64Acos:
1194 ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(acos);
1195 break;
1196 case kIeee754Float64Acosh:
1197 ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(acosh);
1198 break;
1199 case kIeee754Float64Asin:
1200 ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(asin);
1201 break;
1202 case kIeee754Float64Asinh:
1203 ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(asinh);
1204 break;
1205 case kIeee754Float64Atan:
1206 ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(atan);
1207 break;
1208 case kIeee754Float64Atanh:

1741 int offset =
1742 FrameSlotToFPOffset(frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - reverse_slot);
1743 if (instr->OutputAt(0)->IsFPRegister()) {
1744 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(instr->OutputAt(0));
1745 if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
1746 __ Ldr(i.OutputDoubleRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1747 } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1748 __ Ldr(i.OutputFloatRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1749 } else {
1750 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
1751 __ Ldr(i.OutputSimd128Register(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1752 }
1753 } else {
1754 __ Ldr(i.OutputRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1755 }

1937 case kArm64Float32ToInt32: {
1938 __ Fcvtzs(i.OutputRegister32(), i.InputFloat32Register(0));
1939 bool set_overflow_to_min_i32 = MiscField::decode(instr->opcode());
1940 if (set_overflow_to_min_i32) {
1941 // Avoid INT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT32_MIN instead,
1942 // because INT32_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1943 __ Cmn(i.OutputRegister32(), 1);
1944 __ Csinc(i.OutputRegister32(), i.OutputRegister32(),
1945 i.OutputRegister32(), vc);
1946 }

1949 case kArm64Float64ToInt32:
1950 __ Fcvtzs(i.OutputRegister32(), i.InputDoubleRegister(0));
1951 if (i.OutputCount() > 1) {
1952 // Check for inputs below INT32_MIN and NaN.
1953 __ Fcmp(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), static_cast<double>(INT32_MIN));
1954 __ Cset(i.OutputRegister(1).W(), ge);
1955 __ Fcmp(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), static_cast<double>(INT32_MAX) + 1);
1956 __ CmovX(i.OutputRegister(1), xzr, ge);
1957 }
1958 break;
1959 case kArm64Float32ToUint32: {

1962 if (set_overflow_to_min_u32) {
1963 // Avoid UINT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use 0 instead,
1964 // because 0 allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1965 __ Cmn(i.OutputRegister32(), 1);
1966 __ Adc(i.OutputRegister32(), i.OutputRegister32(), Operand(0));

1974 __ Cset(i.OutputRegister(1).W(), gt);

1976 __ CmovX(i.OutputRegister(1), xzr, ge);

1979 case kArm64Float32ToInt64:

1983 __ Fcmp(i.InputFloat32Register(0), static_cast<float>(INT64_MIN));
1984 // Check overflow.
1985 // -1 value is used to indicate a possible overflow which will occur
1986 // when subtracting (-1) from the provided INT64_MAX operand.
1987 // OutputRegister(1) is set to 0 if the input was out of range or NaN.
1988 __ Ccmp(i.OutputRegister(0), -1, VFlag, ge);
1989 __ Cset(i.OutputRegister(1), vc);

2297 __ Sxtb(i.OutputRegister(0), i.OutputRegister(0));
2298 break;
2299 case kAtomicSubUint8:
2300 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_SUB(b, Register32);
2301 break;
2302 case kAtomicSubInt16:

2305 break;
2306 case kAtomicSubUint16:

2308 break;
2309 case kAtomicSubWord32:
2310 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_SUB(, Register32);
2311 break;

2314 break;

2318 break;

2321 break;

2325 break;

2335#define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(op, inst, lse_instr) \
2336 case kAtomic##op##Int8: \
2337 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(b, inst, lse_instr, Register32); \
2338 __ Sxtb(i.OutputRegister(0), i.OutputRegister(0)); \
2339 break; \

2342 break; \

2344 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(h, inst, lse_instr, Register32); \
2345 __ Sxth(i.OutputRegister(0), i.OutputRegister(0)); \
2346 break; \
2347 case kAtomic##op##Uint16: \
2348 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(h, inst, lse_instr, Register32); \
2349 break; \
2350 case kAtomic##op##Word32: \
2351 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(, inst, lse_instr, Register32); \
2352 break; \
2353 case kArm64Word64Atomic##op##Uint64: \
2354 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(, inst, lse_instr, Register); \
2355 break;

2722 SIMD_BINOP_LANE_SIZE_CASE(kArm64IAdd, Add);
2723 SIMD_BINOP_LANE_SIZE_CASE(kArm64ISub, Sub);
2724 case kArm64I64x2Mul: {
2725 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
2726 VRegister dst = i.OutputSimd128Register();
2727 VRegister src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(0);
2728 VRegister src2 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
2729 VRegister tmp1 = scope.AcquireSameSizeAs(dst);
2730 VRegister tmp2 = scope.AcquireSameSizeAs(dst);
2731 VRegister tmp3 = i.ToSimd128Register(instr->TempAt(0));
2732
2733 // This 2x64-bit multiplication is performed with several 32-bit
2734 // multiplications.
2735
2736 // 64-bit numbers x and y, can be represented as:
2737 // x = a + 2^32(b)
2738 // y = c + 2^32(d)
2739
2740 // A 64-bit multiplication is:
2741 // x * y = ac + 2^32(ad + bc) + 2^64(bd)
2742 // note: `2^64(bd)` can be ignored, the value is too large to fit in
2743 // 64-bits.
2744
2745 // This sequence implements a 2x64bit multiply, where the registers
2746 // `src1` and `src2` are split up into 32-bit components:
2747 // src1 = |d|c|b|a|
2748 // src2 = |h|g|f|e|
2749 //
2750 // src1 * src2 = |cg + 2^32(ch + dg)|ae + 2^32(af + be)|
2751
2752 // Reverse the 32-bit elements in the 64-bit words.
2753 // tmp2 = |g|h|e|f|
2754 __ Rev64(tmp2.V4S(), src2.V4S());
2755
2756 // Calculate the high half components.
2757 // tmp2 = |dg|ch|be|af|
2758 __ Mul(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), src1.V4S());
2759
2760 // Extract the low half components of src1.
2761 // tmp1 = |c|a|
2762 __ Xtn(tmp1.V2S(), src1.V2D());
2763
2764 // Sum the respective high half components.
2765 // tmp2 = |dg+ch|be+af||dg+ch|be+af|
2766 __ Addp(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S());
2767
2768 // Extract the low half components of src2.
2769 // tmp3 = |g|e|
2770 __ Xtn(tmp3.V2S(), src2.V2D());

2777 // half.

3106 case kArm64S32x4Shuffle: {
3107 Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register().V4S(),
3108 src0 = i.InputSimd128Register(0).V4S(),
3109 src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(1).V4S();
3110 // Check for in-place shuffles.
3111 // If dst == src0 == src1, then the shuffle is unary and we only use src0.
3112 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
3113 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(kFormat4S);
3114 if (dst == src0) {
3115 __ Mov(temp, src0);
3116 src0 = temp;
3117 } else if (dst == src1) {
3118 __ Mov(temp, src1);
3119 src1 = temp;
3120 }
3121 int32_t shuffle = i.InputInt32(2);
3122
3123 // Check whether we can reduce the number of vmovs by performing a dup
3124 // first.
3125 if (src0 == src1) {
3126 const std::array<int, 4> lanes{shuffle & 0x3, shuffle >> 8 & 0x3,
3127 shuffle >> 16 & 0x3,
3128 shuffle >> 24 & 0x3};
3129 std::array<int, 4> lane_counts{};
3130 for (int lane : lanes) {
3131 ++lane_counts[lane];
3132 }
3133
3134 int duplicate_lane = -1;
3135 for (int lane = 0; lane < 4; ++lane) {
3136 if (lane_counts[lane] > 1) {
3137 duplicate_lane = lane;
3138 break;
3139 }
3140 }
3141
3142 if (duplicate_lane != -1) {
3143 __ Dup(dst, src0, duplicate_lane);
3144 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
3145 int lane = lanes[i];
3146 if (lane == duplicate_lane) continue;
3147 __ Mov(dst, i, src0, lane);
3148 }
3149 break;
3150 }
3151 }
3152
3153 // Perform shuffle as a vmov per lane.
3154 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3155 VRegister src = src0;
3156 int lane = shuffle & 0x7;
3157 if (lane >= 4) {
3158 src = src1;
3159 lane &= 0x3;

3161 __ Mov(dst, i, src, lane);
3162 shuffle >>= 8;
3163 }

3278 case kArm64S128Load32x2S: {
3279 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset());
3280 __ Ldr(i.OutputSimd128Register().V2S(), i.MemoryOperand(0));
3281 __ Sxtl(i.OutputSimd128Register().V2D(), i.OutputSimd128Register().V2S());
3282 break;
3283 }
3284 case kArm64S128Load32x2U: {
3285 RecordTrapInfoIfNeeded(zone(), this, opcode, instr, __ pc_offset());
3286 __ Ldr(i.OutputSimd128Register().V2S(), i.MemoryOperand(0));
3287 __ Uxtl(i.OutputSimd128Register().V2D(), i.OutputSimd128Register().V2S());
3288 break;
3289 }
3290 case kArm64I64x2AllTrue: {
3291 __ I64x2AllTrue(i.OutputRegister32(), i.InputSimd128Register(0));
3292 break;
3293 }
3294 case kArm64V128AnyTrue: {
3295 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
3296 // For AnyTrue, the format does not matter; also, we would like to avoid
3297 // an expensive horizontal reduction.
3298 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(kFormat4S);
3299 __ Umaxp(temp, i.InputSimd128Register(0).V4S(),
3300 i.InputSimd128Register(0).V4S());
3301 __ Fmov(i.OutputRegister64(), temp.D());
3302 __ Cmp(i.OutputRegister64(), 0);
3303 __ Cset(i.OutputRegister32(), ne);
3304 break;
3305 }
3306 case kArm64S32x4OneLaneSwizzle: {
3307 Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register().V4S(),
3308 src = i.InputSimd128Register(0).V4S();
3309 int from = i.InputInt32(1);
3310 int to = i.InputInt32(2);
3311 if (dst != src) {
3312 __ Mov(dst, src);
3313 }
3314 __ Mov(dst, to, src, from);
3315 break;
3316 }
3317#define SIMD_REDUCE_OP_CASE(Op, Instr, format, FORMAT) \
3318 case Op: { \
3319 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm()); \
3320 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(format); \
3321 __ Instr(temp, i.InputSimd128Register(0).V##FORMAT()); \
3322 __ Umov(i.OutputRegister32(), temp, 0); \
3323 __ Cmp(i.OutputRegister32(), 0); \
3324 __ Cset(i.OutputRegister32(), ne); \
3325 break; \
3326 }
3327 SIMD_REDUCE_OP_CASE(kArm64I32x4AllTrue, Uminv, kFormatS, 4S);
3328 SIMD_REDUCE_OP_CASE(kArm64I16x8AllTrue, Uminv, kFormatH, 8H);
3329 SIMD_REDUCE_OP_CASE(kArm64I8x16AllTrue, Uminv, kFormatB, 16B);
3330#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3331 }
3332 return kSuccess;
3333}
3334
3335#undef SIMD_UNOP_CASE
3336#undef SIMD_UNOP_LANE_SIZE_CASE
3337#undef SIMD_BINOP_CASE
3338#undef SIMD_BINOP_LANE_SIZE_CASE
3339#undef SIMD_DESTRUCTIVE_BINOP_CASE
3340#undef SIMD_DESTRUCTIVE_BINOP_LANE_SIZE_CASE
3341#undef SIMD_DESTRUCTIVE_RELAXED_FUSED_CASE
3342#undef SIMD_REDUCE_OP_CASE
3343#undef ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_LEFT
3344#undef ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_RIGHT

3346// Assemble branches after this instruction.
3347void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBranch(Instruction* instr, BranchInfo* branch) {
3348 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3349 Label* tlabel = branch->true_label;
3350 Label* flabel = branch->false_label;
3351 FlagsCondition condition = branch->condition;
3352 ArchOpcode opcode = instr->arch_opcode();
3353
3354 if (opcode == kArm64CompareAndBranch32) {
3355 switch (condition) {
3356 case kEqual:
3357 __ Cbz(i.InputRegister32(0), tlabel);
3358 break;
3359 case kNotEqual:
3360 __ Cbnz(i.InputRegister32(0), tlabel);
3361 break;
3362 default:
3363 UNREACHABLE();
3364 }
3365 } else if (opcode == kArm64CompareAndBranch) {
3366 switch (condition) {
3367 case kEqual:
3368 __ Cbz(i.InputRegister64(0), tlabel);
3369 break;
3370 case kNotEqual:
3371 __ Cbnz(i.InputRegister64(0), tlabel);
3372 break;
3373 default:
3374 UNREACHABLE();
3375 }
3376 } else if (opcode == kArm64TestAndBranch32) {
3377 switch (condition) {
3378 case kEqual:
3379 __ Tbz(i.InputRegister32(0), i.InputInt5(1), tlabel);
3380 break;
3381 case kNotEqual:
3382 __ Tbnz(i.InputRegister32(0), i.InputInt5(1), tlabel);
3383 break;
3384 default:
3385 UNREACHABLE();
3386 }
3387 } else if (opcode == kArm64TestAndBranch) {
3388 switch (condition) {
3389 case kEqual:
3390 __ Tbz(i.InputRegister64(0), i.InputInt6(1), tlabel);
3391 break;
3392 case kNotEqual:
3393 __ Tbnz(i.InputRegister64(0), i.InputInt6(1), tlabel);
3394 break;
3395 default:
3396 UNREACHABLE();
3397 }
3398 } else {
3399 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3400 __ B(cc, tlabel);
3401 }
3402 if (!branch->fallthru) __ B(flabel); // no fallthru to flabel.
3403}
3404
3405void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchDeoptBranch(Instruction* instr,
3406 BranchInfo* branch) {
3407 AssembleArchBranch(instr, branch);
3408}

3425// Assemble boolean materializations after this instruction.
3426void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBoolean(Instruction* instr,
3427 FlagsCondition condition) {
3428 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3429
3430 // Materialize a full 64-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3431 // last output of the instruction.
3432 DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3433 Register reg = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3434 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3435 __ Cset(reg, cc);
3436}
3437
3438// Given condition, return a value for nzcv which represents it. This is used
3439// for the default condition for ccmp.
3440inline StatusFlags ConditionToDefaultFlags(Condition condition) {
3441 switch (condition) {
3442 default:
3443 UNREACHABLE();
3444 case eq:
3445 return ZFlag; // Z == 1
3446 case ne:
3447 return NoFlag; // Z == 0
3448 case hs:
3449 return CFlag; // C == 1
3450 case lo:
3451 return NoFlag; // C == 0
3452 case mi:
3453 return NFlag; // N == 1
3454 case pl:
3455 return NoFlag; // N == 0
3456 case vs:
3457 return VFlag; // V == 1
3458 case vc:
3459 return NoFlag; // V == 0
3460 case hi:
3461 return CFlag; // C == 1 && Z == 0
3462 case ls:
3463 return NoFlag; // C == 0 || Z == 1
3464 case ge:
3465 return NoFlag; // N == V
3466 case lt:
3467 return NFlag; // N != V
3468 case gt:
3469 return NoFlag; // Z == 0 && N == V
3470 case le:
3471 return ZFlag; // Z == 1 || N != V
3472 }
3473}
3474
3475void AssembleConditionalCompareChain(Instruction* instr, int64_t num_ccmps,
3476 size_t ccmp_base_index,
3477 CodeGenerator* gen) {
3478 Arm64OperandConverter i(gen, instr);
3479 // The first two, or three operands are the compare that begins the chain.
3480 // These operands are used when the first compare, the one with the
3481 // continuation attached, is generated.
3482 // Then, each five provide:
3483 // - cmp opcode
3484 // - compare lhs
3485 // - compare rhs
3486 // - default flags
3487 // - user condition
3488 for (unsigned n = 0; n < num_ccmps; ++n) {
3489 size_t opcode_index = ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfOpcode;
3490 size_t compare_lhs_index = ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfLhs;
3491 size_t compare_rhs_index = ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfRhs;
3492 size_t default_condition_index =
3493 ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfDefaultFlags;
3494 size_t compare_condition_index =
3495 ccmp_base_index + kCcmpOffsetOfCompareCondition;
3496 ccmp_base_index += kNumCcmpOperands;
3497 DCHECK_LT(ccmp_base_index, instr->InputCount() - 1);
3498
3499 InstructionCode code = static_cast<InstructionCode>(
3500 i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(opcode_index)).ToInt64());
3501
3502 FlagsCondition default_condition = static_cast<FlagsCondition>(
3503 i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(default_condition_index)).ToInt64());
3504
3505 StatusFlags default_flags =
3506 ConditionToDefaultFlags(FlagsConditionToCondition(default_condition));
3507
3508 FlagsCondition compare_condition = static_cast<FlagsCondition>(
3509 i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(compare_condition_index)).ToInt64());
3510
3511 if (code == kArm64Cmp) {
3512 gen->masm()->Ccmp(i.InputRegister64(compare_lhs_index),
3513 i.InputOperand64(compare_rhs_index), default_flags,
3514 FlagsConditionToCondition(compare_condition));
3515 } else {
3516 DCHECK_EQ(code, kArm64Cmp32);
3517 gen->masm()->Ccmp(i.InputRegister32(compare_lhs_index),
3518 i.InputOperand32(compare_rhs_index), default_flags,
3519 FlagsConditionToCondition(compare_condition));
3520 }
3521 }
3522}
3523
3524// Assemble a conditional compare and boolean materializations after this
3525// instruction.
3526void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchConditionalBoolean(Instruction* instr) {
3527 // Materialize a full 64-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3528 // last output of the instruction.
3529 DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3530 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3531 Register reg = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3532 DCHECK_GE(instr->InputCount(), 6);
3533
3534 // Input ordering:
3535 // > InputCount - 1: number of ccmps.
3536 // > InputCount - 2: branch condition.
3537 size_t num_ccmps_index =
3538 instr->InputCount() - kConditionalSetEndOffsetOfNumCcmps;
3539 size_t set_condition_index =
3540 instr->InputCount() - kConditionalSetEndOffsetOfCondition;
3541 int64_t num_ccmps = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(num_ccmps_index)).ToInt64();
3542 size_t ccmp_base_index = set_condition_index - kNumCcmpOperands * num_ccmps;
3543 AssembleConditionalCompareChain(instr, num_ccmps, ccmp_base_index, this);
3544
3545 FlagsCondition set_condition = static_cast<FlagsCondition>(
3546 i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(set_condition_index)).ToInt64());
3547 __ Cset(reg, FlagsConditionToCondition(set_condition));
3548}
3549
3550void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchConditionalBranch(Instruction* instr,
3551 BranchInfo* branch) {
3552 DCHECK_GE(instr->InputCount(), 6);
3553 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3554 // Input ordering:
3555 // > InputCount - 1: false block.
3556 // > InputCount - 2: true block.
3557 // > InputCount - 3: number of ccmps.
3558 // > InputCount - 4: branch condition.
3559 size_t num_ccmps_index =
3560 instr->InputCount() - kConditionalBranchEndOffsetOfNumCcmps;
3561 int64_t num_ccmps = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(num_ccmps_index)).ToInt64();
3562 size_t ccmp_base_index = instr->InputCount() -
3563 kConditionalBranchEndOffsetOfCondition -
3564 kNumCcmpOperands * num_ccmps;
3565 AssembleConditionalCompareChain(instr, num_ccmps, ccmp_base_index, this);
3566 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(branch->condition);
3567 __ B(cc, branch->true_label);
3568 if (!branch->fallthru) __ B(branch->false_label);
3569}
3570
3571void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchSelect(Instruction* instr,
3572 FlagsCondition condition) {
3573 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3574 // The result register is always the last output of the instruction.
3575 size_t output_index = instr->OutputCount() - 1;
3576 MachineRepresentation rep =
3577 LocationOperand::cast(instr->OutputAt(output_index))->representation();
3578 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition);
3579 // We don't now how many inputs were consumed by the condition, so we have to
3580 // calculate the indices of the last two inputs.
3581 DCHECK_GE(instr->InputCount(), 2);
3582 size_t true_value_index = instr->InputCount() - 2;
3583 size_t false_value_index = instr->InputCount() - 1;
3584 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
3585 __ Fcsel(i.OutputFloat32Register(output_index),
3586 i.InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(true_value_index),
3587 i.InputFloat32OrFPZeroRegister(false_value_index), cc);
3588 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3589 __ Fcsel(i.OutputFloat64Register(output_index),
3590 i.InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(true_value_index),
3591 i.InputFloat64OrFPZeroRegister(false_value_index), cc);
3592 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
3593 __ Csel(i.OutputRegister32(output_index),
3594 i.InputOrZeroRegister32(true_value_index),
3595 i.InputOrZeroRegister32(false_value_index), cc);
3596 } else {
3597 DCHECK_EQ(rep, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3598 __ Csel(i.OutputRegister64(output_index),
3599 i.InputOrZeroRegister64(true_value_index),
3600 i.InputOrZeroRegister64(false_value_index), cc);
3601 }
3602}
3603
3604void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitch(Instruction* instr) {
3605 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3606 Register input = i.InputRegister32(0);
3607 std::vector<std::pair<int32_t, Label*>> cases;
3608 for (size_t index = 2; index < instr->InputCount(); index += 2) {
3609 cases.push_back({i.InputInt32(index + 0), GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 1))});
3610 }
3611 AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitchRange(input, i.InputRpo(1), cases.data(),
3612 cases.data() + cases.size());
3613}
3614
3615void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchTableSwitch(Instruction* instr) {
3616 Arm64OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3617 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
3618 Register input = i.InputRegister64(0);
3619 size_t const case_count = instr->InputCount() - 2;
3620
3621 base::Vector<Label*> cases = zone()->AllocateVector<Label*>(case_count);
3622 for (size_t index = 0; index < case_count; ++index) {
3623 cases[index] = GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 2));
3624 }
3625 Label* fallthrough = GetLabel(i.InputRpo(1));
3626 __ Cmp(input, Immediate(case_count));
3627 __ B(fallthrough, hs);
3628
3629 Label* const jump_table = AddJumpTable(cases);
3630 Register addr = scope.AcquireX();
3631 __ Adr(addr, jump_table, MacroAssembler::kAdrFar);
3632 Register offset = scope.AcquireX();
3633 // Load the 32-bit offset.
3634 __ Ldrsw(offset, MemOperand(addr, input, LSL, 2));
3635 // The offset is relative to the address of 'jump_table', so add 'offset'
3636 // to 'addr' to reconstruct the absolute address.
3637 __ Add(addr, addr, offset);
3638 __ Br(addr);
3639}
3640
3641void CodeGenerator::AssembleJumpTable(base::Vector<Label*> targets) {
3642 const size_t jump_table_size = targets.size() * kInt32Size;
3643 MacroAssembler::BlockPoolsScope no_pool_inbetween(masm(), jump_table_size);
3644 int table_pos = __ pc_offset();
3645 // Store 32-bit pc-relative offsets.
3646 for (auto* target : targets) {
3647 __ dc32(target->pos() - table_pos);
3648 }
3649}
3650
3651void CodeGenerator::FinishFrame(Frame* frame) {
3652 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3653
3654 // Save FP registers.
3655 CPURegList saves_fp =
3656 CPURegList(kDRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters());
3657 int saved_count = saves_fp.Count();
3658 if (saved_count != 0) {
3659 DCHECK(saves_fp.bits() == CPURegList::GetCalleeSavedV().bits());
3660 frame->AllocateSavedCalleeRegisterSlots(saved_count *
3661 (kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize));
3662 }
3663
3664 CPURegList saves =
3665 CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters());
3666 saved_count = saves.Count();
3667 if (saved_count != 0) {
3668 frame->AllocateSavedCalleeRegisterSlots(saved_count);
3669 }
3670 frame->AlignFrame(16);
3671}
3672
3673void CodeGenerator::AssembleConstructFrame() {
3674 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3675 __ AssertSpAligned();
3676
3677 // The frame has been previously padded in CodeGenerator::FinishFrame().
3678 DCHECK_EQ(frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() % 2, 0);
3679 int required_slots =
3680 frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - frame()->GetFixedSlotCount();
3681
3682 CPURegList saves =
3683 CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters());
3684 DCHECK_EQ(saves.Count() % 2, 0);
3685 CPURegList saves_fp =
3686 CPURegList(kDRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters());
3687 DCHECK_EQ(saves_fp.Count() % 2, 0);
3688 // The number of return slots should be even after aligning the Frame.
3689 const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3690 DCHECK_EQ(returns % 2, 0);
3691
3692 if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3693 // Link the frame
3694 if (call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall()) {
3695 static_assert(StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize % 16 == 8);
3696 DCHECK_EQ(required_slots % 2, 1);
3697 __ Prologue();
3698 // Update required_slots count since we have just claimed one extra slot.
3699 static_assert(MacroAssembler::kExtraSlotClaimedByPrologue == 1);
3700 required_slots -= MacroAssembler::kExtraSlotClaimedByPrologue;
3701#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3702 } else if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() ||
3703 call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction() ||
3704 call_descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
3705 (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall() &&
3706 info()->GetOutputStackFrameType() ==
3707 StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY)) {
3708 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3709 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3710 __ Mov(scratch,
3711 StackFrame::TypeToMarker(info()->GetOutputStackFrameType()));
3712 __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, fp, scratch,
3713 kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3714 static constexpr int kSPToFPDelta = 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
3715 __ Add(fp, sp, kSPToFPDelta);
3716 if (call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
3717 // The C-API function has one extra slot for the PC.
3718 required_slots++;
3719 }
3720#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3721 } else if (call_descriptor->kind() == CallDescriptor::kCallCodeObject) {
3722 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3723 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3724 __ Mov(scratch,
3725 StackFrame::TypeToMarker(info()->GetOutputStackFrameType()));
3726 __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, fp, scratch, padreg);
3727 static constexpr int kSPToFPDelta = 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
3728 __ Add(fp, sp, kSPToFPDelta);
3729 // One of the extra slots has just been claimed when pushing the padreg.
3730 // We also know that we have at least one slot to claim here, as the typed
3731 // frame has an odd number of fixed slots, and all other parts of the
3732 // total frame slots are even, leaving {required_slots} to be odd.
3733 DCHECK_GE(required_slots, 1);
3734 required_slots--;
3735 } else {
3736 __ Push<MacroAssembler::kSignLR>(lr, fp);
3737 __ Mov(fp, sp);
3738 }
3739 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkFrameConstructed(__ pc_offset());
3740
3741 // Create OSR entry if applicable
3742 if (info()->is_osr()) {
3743 // TurboFan OSR-compiled functions cannot be entered directly.
3744 __ Abort(AbortReason::kShouldNotDirectlyEnterOsrFunction);
3745
3746 // Unoptimized code jumps directly to this entrypoint while the
3747 // unoptimized frame is still on the stack. Optimized code uses OSR values
3748 // directly from the unoptimized frame. Thus, all that needs to be done is
3749 // to allocate the remaining stack slots.
3750 __ RecordComment("-- OSR entrypoint --");
3751 osr_pc_offset_ = __ pc_offset();
3752 __ CodeEntry();
3753 size_t unoptimized_frame_slots = osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots();
3754
3755#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL
3756 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3757 uint32_t expected_frame_size =
3758 static_cast<uint32_t>(osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots()) *
3759 kSystemPointerSize +
3760 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
3761 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3762 __ Add(scratch, sp, expected_frame_size);
3763 __ Cmp(scratch, fp);
3764 __ SbxCheck(eq, AbortReason::kOsrUnexpectedStackSize);
3765#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL
3766
3767 DCHECK(call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall());
3768 DCHECK_EQ(unoptimized_frame_slots % 2, 1);
3769 // One unoptimized frame slot has already been claimed when the actual
3770 // arguments count was pushed.
3771 required_slots -=
3772 unoptimized_frame_slots - MacroAssembler::kExtraSlotClaimedByPrologue;
3773 }
3774
3775#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3776 if (info()->IsWasm() && required_slots * kSystemPointerSize > 4 * KB) {
3777 // For WebAssembly functions with big frames we have to do the stack
3778 // overflow check before we construct the frame. Otherwise we may not
3779 // have enough space on the stack to call the runtime for the stack
3780 // overflow.
3781 Label done;
3782 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
3783 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
3784 // check in the condition code.
3785 if (required_slots * kSystemPointerSize < v8_flags.stack_size * KB) {
3786 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3787 Register stack_limit = temps.AcquireX();
3788 __ LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
3789 __ Add(stack_limit, stack_limit, required_slots * kSystemPointerSize);
3790 __ Cmp(sp, stack_limit);
3791 __ B(hs, &done);
3792 }
3793
3794 if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
3795 CPURegList regs_to_save(kXRegSizeInBits, RegList{});
3796 regs_to_save.Combine(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
3797 regs_to_save.Combine(
3798 WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
3799 for (auto reg : wasm::kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
3800 __ PushCPURegList(regs_to_save);
3801 CPURegList fp_regs_to_save(kDRegSizeInBits, DoubleRegList{});
3802 for (auto reg : wasm::kFpParamRegisters) fp_regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
3803 __ PushCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
3804 __ Mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(),
3805 required_slots * kSystemPointerSize);
3806 __ Add(
3807 WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
3808 Operand(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount() * kSystemPointerSize +
3809 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
3810 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
3811 __ PopCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
3812 __ PopCPURegList(regs_to_save);
3813 } else {
3814 __ Call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
3815 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
3816 // The call does not return, hence we can ignore any references and just
3817 // define an empty safepoint.
3818 ReferenceMap* reference_map = zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(zone());
3819 RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
3820 if (v8_flags.debug_code) __ Brk(0);
3821 }
3822 __ Bind(&done);
3823 }
3824#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3825
3826 // Skip callee-saved slots, which are pushed below.
3827 required_slots -= saves.Count();
3828 required_slots -= saves_fp.Count();
3829 required_slots -= returns;
3830
3831 __ Claim(required_slots);
3832 }
3833
3834 // Save FP registers.
3835 DCHECK_IMPLIES(saves_fp.Count() != 0,
3836 saves_fp.bits() == CPURegList::GetCalleeSavedV().bits());
3837 __ PushCPURegList(saves_fp);
3838
3839 // Save registers.
3840 __ PushCPURegList(saves);
3841
3842 if (returns != 0) {
3843 __ Claim(returns);
3844 }
3845
3846 for (int spill_slot : frame()->tagged_slots()) {
3847 FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(spill_slot);
3848 DCHECK(offset.from_frame_pointer());
3849 __ Str(xzr, MemOperand(fp, offset.offset()));
3850 }
3851}
3852
3853void CodeGenerator::AssembleReturn(InstructionOperand* additional_pop_count) {
3854 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3855
3856 const int returns = RoundUp(frame()->GetReturnSlotCount(), 2);
3857 if (returns != 0) {
3858 __ Drop(returns);
3859 }
3860
3861 // Restore registers.
3862 CPURegList saves =
3863 CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters());
3864 __ PopCPURegList(saves);
3865
3866 // Restore fp registers.
3867 CPURegList saves_fp =
3868 CPURegList(kDRegSizeInBits, call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters());
3869 __ PopCPURegList(saves_fp);
3870
3871 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
3872
3873 const int parameter_slots =
3874 static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount());
3875 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3876
3877 // {aditional_pop_count} is only greater than zero if {parameter_slots = 0}.
3878 // Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
3879 if (parameter_slots != 0) {
3880 if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
3881 DCHECK_EQ(g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32(), 0);
3882 } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3883 __ cmp(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count), Operand(0));
3884 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedAdditionalPopValue);
3885 }
3886 }
3887
3888#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3889 if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() &&
3890 v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
3891 {
3892 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{masm()};
3893 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
3894 __ Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
3895 __ Cmp(scratch,
3896 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
3897 }
3898 Label done;
3899 __ B(ne, &done);
3900 CPURegList regs_to_save(kXRegSizeInBits, RegList{});
3901 for (auto reg : wasm::kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
3902 __ PushCPURegList(regs_to_save);
3903 CPURegList fp_regs_to_save(kDRegSizeInBits, DoubleRegList{});
3904 for (auto reg : wasm::kFpReturnRegisters) fp_regs_to_save.Combine(reg);
3905 __ PushCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
3906 __ Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
3907 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
3908 __ Mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
3909 __ PopCPURegList(fp_regs_to_save);
3910 __ PopCPURegList(regs_to_save);
3911 if (masm()->options().enable_simulator_code) {
3912 // The next instruction after shrinking stack is leaving the frame.
3913 // So SP will be set to old FP there. Switch simulator stack limit here.
3914 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{masm()};
3915 temps.Exclude(x16);
3916 __ LoadStackLimit(x16, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
3917 __ hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
3918 }
3919 __ bind(&done);
3920 }
3921#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3922
3923 Register argc_reg = x3;
3924 // Functions with JS linkage have at least one parameter (the receiver).
3925 // If {parameter_slots} == 0, it means it is a builtin with
3926 // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel, which takes care of JS arguments popping
3927 // itself.
3928 const bool drop_jsargs = parameter_slots != 0 &&
3929 frame_access_state()->has_frame() &&
3930 call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall();
3931 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3932 AssembleDeconstructFrame();
3933 } else if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3934 // Canonicalize JSFunction return sites for now unless they have an variable
3935 // number of stack slot pops.
3936 if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate() &&
3937 g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32() == 0) {
3938 if (return_label_.is_bound()) {
3939 __ B(&return_label_);
3940 return;
3941 } else {
3942 __ Bind(&return_label_);
3943 }
3944 }
3945 if (drop_jsargs) {
3946 // Get the actual argument count.
3947 DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
3948 __ Ldr(argc_reg, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
3949 }
3950 AssembleDeconstructFrame();
3951 }
3952
3953 if (drop_jsargs) {
3954 // We must pop all arguments from the stack (including the receiver). This
3955 // number of arguments is given by max(1 + argc_reg, parameter_slots).
3956 Label argc_reg_has_final_count;
3957 DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
3958 if (parameter_slots > 1) {
3959 __ Cmp(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
3960 __ B(&argc_reg_has_final_count, ge);
3961 __ Mov(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
3962 __ Bind(&argc_reg_has_final_count);
3963 }
3964 __ DropArguments(argc_reg);
3965 } else if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
3966 int additional_count = g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32();
3967 __ DropArguments(parameter_slots + additional_count);
3968 } else if (parameter_slots == 0) {
3969 __ DropArguments(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count));
3970 } else {
3971 // {additional_pop_count} is guaranteed to be zero if {parameter_slots !=
3972 // 0}. Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
3973 __ DropArguments(parameter_slots);
3974 }
3975 __ AssertSpAligned();
3976 __ Ret();
3977}

3979void CodeGenerator::FinishCode() { __ ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump(); }
3980
3981void CodeGenerator::PrepareForDeoptimizationExits(
3982 ZoneDeque<DeoptimizationExit*>* exits) {
3983 __ ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
3984 // We are conservative here, reserving sufficient space for the largest deopt
3985 // kind.
3986 DCHECK_GE(Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize, Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
3987 __ CheckVeneerPool(
3988 false, false,
3989 static_cast<int>(exits->size()) * Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize);
3990
3991 // Check which deopt kinds exist in this InstructionStream object, to avoid
3992 // emitting jumps to unused entries.
3993 bool saw_deopt_kind[kDeoptimizeKindCount] = {false};
3994 for (auto exit : *exits) {
3995 saw_deopt_kind[static_cast<int>(exit->kind())] = true;
3996 }
3997
3998 // Emit the jumps to deoptimization entries.
3999 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4000 Register scratch = scope.AcquireX();
4001 static_assert(static_cast<int>(kFirstDeoptimizeKind) == 0);
4002 for (int i = 0; i < kDeoptimizeKindCount; i++) {
4003 if (!saw_deopt_kind[i]) continue;
4004 DeoptimizeKind kind = static_cast<DeoptimizeKind>(i);
4005 __ bind(&jump_deoptimization_entry_labels_[i]);
4006 __ LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Deoptimizer::GetDeoptimizationEntry(kind), scratch);
4007 __ Jump(scratch);
4008 }
4009}
