4011AllocatedOperand CodeGenerator::Push(InstructionOperand* source) {
4012 auto rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4013 int new_slots = RoundUp<2>(ElementSizeInPointers(rep));
4014 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4015 int last_frame_slot_id =
4016 frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
4017 int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
4018 int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta + new_slots;
4019 AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
4020 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4021 __ Push(padreg, g.ToRegister(source));
4022 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4023 } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4024 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4025 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
4026 __ Ldr(scratch, g.ToMemOperand(source, masm()));
4027 __ Push(padreg, scratch);
4028 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4029 } else {
4030 // No push instruction for this operand type. Bump the stack pointer and
4031 // assemble the move.
4032 __ Sub(sp, sp, Operand(new_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4033 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4034 AssembleMove(source, &stack_slot);
4035 }
4036 temp_slots_ += new_slots;
4037 return stack_slot;
4038}
4039
4040void CodeGenerator::Pop(InstructionOperand* dest, MachineRepresentation rep) {
4041 int dropped_slots = RoundUp<2>(ElementSizeInPointers(rep));
4042 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4043 if (dest->IsRegister()) {
4044 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4045 __ Pop(g.ToRegister(dest), padreg);
4046 } else if (dest->IsStackSlot()) {
4047 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4048 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4049 Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
4050 __ Pop(scratch, padreg);
4051 __ Str(scratch, g.ToMemOperand(dest, masm()));
4052 } else {
4053 int last_frame_slot_id =
4054 frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
4055 int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
4056 int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta;
4057 AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
4058 AssembleMove(&stack_slot, dest);
4059 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4060 __ Add(sp, sp, Operand(dropped_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4061 }
4062 temp_slots_ -= dropped_slots;
4063}
4064
4065void CodeGenerator::PopTempStackSlots() {
4066 if (temp_slots_ > 0) {
4067 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-temp_slots_);
4068 __ add(sp, sp, Operand(temp_slots_ * kSystemPointerSize));
4069 temp_slots_ = 0;
4070 }
4071}

4073void CodeGenerator::MoveToTempLocation(InstructionOperand* source,
4074 MachineRepresentation rep) {
4075 // Must be kept in sync with {MoveTempLocationTo}.
4076 DCHECK(!source->IsImmediate());
4077 move_cycle_.temps.emplace(masm());
4078 auto& temps = *move_cycle_.temps;
4079 // Temporarily exclude the reserved scratch registers while we pick one to
4080 // resolve the move cycle. Re-include them immediately afterwards as they
4081 // might be needed for the move to the temp location.
4082 temps.Exclude(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_regs));
4083 temps.ExcludeFP(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_fp_regs));
4084 if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep)) {
4085 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
4086 Register scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireX();
4087 move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4088 } else if (temps.CanAcquireFP()) {
4089 // Try to use an FP register if no GP register is available for non-FP
4090 // moves.
4091 DoubleRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireD();
4092 move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4093 }
4094 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
4095 VRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireS();
4096 move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4097 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
4098 VRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireD();
4099 move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4100 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4101 VRegister scratch = move_cycle_.temps->AcquireQ();
4102 move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4103 }
4104 temps.Include(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_regs));
4105 temps.IncludeFP(CPURegList(64, move_cycle_.scratch_fp_regs));
4106 if (move_cycle_.scratch_reg.has_value()) {
4107 // A scratch register is available for this rep.
4108 auto& scratch_reg = *move_cycle_.scratch_reg;
4109 if (scratch_reg.IsD() && !IsFloatingPoint(rep)) {
4110 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER,
4111 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
4112 scratch_reg.code());
4113 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4114 if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4115 __ Ldr(g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch), g.ToMemOperand(source, masm()));
4116 } else {
4117 DCHECK(source->IsRegister());
4118 __ fmov(g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch), g.ToRegister(source));
4119 }
4120 } else {
4121 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep,
4122 move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4123 AssembleMove(source, &scratch);
4124 }
4125 } else {
4126 // The scratch registers are blocked by pending moves. Use the stack
4127 // instead.
4128 Push(source);
4129 }
4130}
4131
4132void CodeGenerator::MoveTempLocationTo(InstructionOperand* dest,
4133 MachineRepresentation rep) {
4134 if (move_cycle_.scratch_reg.has_value()) {
4135 auto& scratch_reg = *move_cycle_.scratch_reg;
4136 if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep) && scratch_reg.IsD()) {
4137 // We used a D register to move a non-FP operand, change the
4138 // representation to correctly interpret the InstructionOperand's code.
4139 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER,
4140 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
4141 move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4142 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4143 if (dest->IsStackSlot()) {
4144 __ Str(g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch), g.ToMemOperand(dest, masm()));
4145 } else {
4146 DCHECK(dest->IsRegister());
4147 __ fmov(g.ToRegister(dest), g.ToDoubleRegister(&scratch));
4148 }
4149 } else {
4150 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep,
4151 move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4152 AssembleMove(&scratch, dest);
4153 }
4154 } else {
4155 Pop(dest, rep);
4156 }
4157 // Restore the default state to release the {UseScratchRegisterScope} and to
4158 // prepare for the next cycle.
4159 move_cycle_ = MoveCycleState();
4160}

4162void CodeGenerator::SetPendingMove(MoveOperands* move) {
4163 auto move_type = MoveType::InferMove(&move->source(), &move->destination());
4164 if (move_type == MoveType::kStackToStack) {
4165 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4166 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(&move->source(), masm());
4167 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(&move->destination(), masm());
4168 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4169 if (move->source().IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
4170 VRegister temp = temps.AcquireQ();
4171 move_cycle_.scratch_fp_regs.set(temp);
4172 } else {
4173 Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
4174 move_cycle_.scratch_regs.set(temp);
4175 }
4176 int64_t src_offset = src.offset();
4177 unsigned src_size_log2 = CalcLSDataSizeLog2(LDR_x);
4178 int64_t dst_offset = dst.offset();
4179 unsigned dst_size_log2 = CalcLSDataSizeLog2(STR_x);
4180 // Offset doesn't fit into the immediate field so the assembler will emit
4181 // two instructions and use a second temp register.
4182 if ((src.IsImmediateOffset() &&
4183 !masm()->IsImmLSScaled(src_offset, src_size_log2) &&
4184 !masm()->IsImmLSUnscaled(src_offset)) ||
4185 (dst.IsImmediateOffset() &&
4186 !masm()->IsImmLSScaled(dst_offset, dst_size_log2) &&
4187 !masm()->IsImmLSUnscaled(dst_offset))) {
4188 Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
4189 move_cycle_.scratch_regs.set(temp);
4190 }
4191 }
4192}

4194void CodeGenerator::AssembleMove(InstructionOperand* source,
4195 InstructionOperand* destination) {
4196 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4197 // Helper function to write the given constant to the dst register.
4198 auto MoveConstantToRegister = [&](Register dst, Constant src) {
4199 if (src.type() == Constant::kHeapObject) {
4200 Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
4201 RootIndex index;
4202 if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
4203 __ LoadRoot(dst, index);
4204 } else {
4205 __ Mov(dst, src_object);
4206 }
4207 } else if (src.type() == Constant::kCompressedHeapObject) {
4208 Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
4209 RootIndex index;
4210 if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
4211 __ LoadTaggedRoot(dst, index);
4212 } else {
4213 // TODO(v8:8977): Even though this mov happens on 32 bits (Note the
4214 // .W()) and we are passing along the RelocInfo, we still haven't made
4215 // the address embedded in the code-stream actually be compressed.
4216 __ Mov(dst.W(),
4217 Immediate(src_object, RelocInfo::COMPRESSED_EMBEDDED_OBJECT));
4218 }
4219 } else if (src.type() == Constant::kExternalReference) {
4220 __ Mov(dst, src.ToExternalReference());
4221 } else {
4222 Operand src_op = g.ToImmediate(source);
4223 if (src.type() == Constant::kInt32 && src_op.NeedsRelocation(masm())) {
4224 // Use 32-bit loads for relocatable 32-bit constants.
4225 dst = dst.W();
4226 }
4227 __ Mov(dst, src_op);
4228 }
4229 };
4230 switch (MoveType::InferMove(source, destination)) {
4231 case MoveType::kRegisterToRegister:
4232 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4233 __ Mov(g.ToRegister(destination), g.ToRegister(source));
4234 } else {
4235 DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register() || source->IsFloatRegister() ||
4236 source->IsDoubleRegister());
4237 __ Mov(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination).Q(),
4238 g.ToDoubleRegister(source).Q());
4239 }
4240 return;
4241 case MoveType::kRegisterToStack: {
4242 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4243 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4244 __ Str(g.ToRegister(source), dst);
4245 } else {
4246 VRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
4247 if (source->IsFloatRegister() || source->IsDoubleRegister()) {
4248 __ Str(src, dst);
4249 } else {
4250 DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register());
4251 __ Str(src.Q(), dst);
4252 }
4253 }
4254 return;
4255 }
4256 case MoveType::kStackToRegister: {
4257 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source, masm());
4258 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4259 __ Ldr(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4260 } else {
4261 VRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4262 if (destination->IsFloatRegister() || destination->IsDoubleRegister()) {
4263 __ Ldr(dst, src);
4264 } else {
4265 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128Register());
4266 __ Ldr(dst.Q(), src);
4267 }
4268 }
4269 return;
4270 }
4271 case MoveType::kStackToStack: {
4272 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source, masm());
4273 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4274 if (source->IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
4275 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4276 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireQ();
4277 __ Ldr(temp, src);
4278 __ Str(temp, dst);
4279 } else {
4280 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4281 Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
4282 __ Ldr(temp, src);
4283 __ Str(temp, dst);
4284 }
4285 return;
4286 }
4287 case MoveType::kConstantToRegister: {
4288 Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
4289 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4290 MoveConstantToRegister(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4291 } else {
4292 VRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4293 if (destination->IsFloatRegister()) {
4294 __ Fmov(dst.S(), src.ToFloat32());
4295 } else {
4296 DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleRegister());
4297 __ Fmov(dst, src.ToFloat64().value());
4298 }
4299 }
4300 return;
4301 }
4302 case MoveType::kConstantToStack: {
4303 Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
4304 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4305 if (destination->IsStackSlot()) {
4306 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4307 Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
4308 MoveConstantToRegister(temp, src);
4309 __ Str(temp, dst);
4310 } else if (destination->IsFloatStackSlot()) {
4311 if (base::bit_cast<int32_t>(src.ToFloat32()) == 0) {
4312 __ Str(wzr, dst);
4313 } else {
4314 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4315 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireS();
4316 __ Fmov(temp, src.ToFloat32());
4317 __ Str(temp, dst);
4318 }
4319 } else {
4320 DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleStackSlot());
4321 if (src.ToFloat64().AsUint64() == 0) {
4322 __ Str(xzr, dst);
4323 } else {
4324 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4325 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireD();
4326 __ Fmov(temp, src.ToFloat64().value());
4327 __ Str(temp, dst);
4328 }
4329 }
4330 return;
4331 }
4332 }
4333 UNREACHABLE();
4334}
4335
4336void CodeGenerator::AssembleSwap(InstructionOperand* source,
4337 InstructionOperand* destination) {
4338 Arm64OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4339 switch (MoveType::InferSwap(source, destination)) {
4340 case MoveType::kRegisterToRegister:
4341 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4342 __ Swap(g.ToRegister(source), g.ToRegister(destination));
4343 } else {
4344 VRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
4345 VRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4346 if (source->IsFloatRegister() || source->IsDoubleRegister()) {
4347 __ Swap(src, dst);
4348 } else {
4349 DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register());
4350 __ Swap(src.Q(), dst.Q());
4351 }
4352 }
4353 return;
4354 case MoveType::kRegisterToStack: {
4355 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4356 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4357 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4358 Register temp = scope.AcquireX();
4359 Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
4360 __ Mov(temp, src);
4361 __ Ldr(src, dst);
4362 __ Str(temp, dst);
4363 } else {
4364 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4365 VRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
4366 if (source->IsFloatRegister() || source->IsDoubleRegister()) {
4367 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireD();
4368 __ Mov(temp, src);
4369 __ Ldr(src, dst);
4370 __ Str(temp, dst);
4371 } else {
4372 DCHECK(source->IsSimd128Register());
4373 VRegister temp = scope.AcquireQ();
4374 __ Mov(temp, src.Q());
4375 __ Ldr(src.Q(), dst);
4376 __ Str(temp, dst);
4377 }
4378 }
4379 return;
4380 }
4381 case MoveType::kStackToStack: {
4382 UseScratchRegisterScope scope(masm());
4383 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source, masm());
4384 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination, masm());
4385 VRegister temp_0 = scope.AcquireD();
4386 VRegister temp_1 = scope.AcquireD();
4387 if (source->IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
4388 __ Ldr(temp_0.Q(), src);
4389 __ Ldr(temp_1.Q(), dst);
4390 __ Str(temp_0.Q(), dst);
4391 __ Str(temp_1.Q(), src);
4392 } else {
4393 __ Ldr(temp_0, src);
4394 __ Ldr(temp_1, dst);
4395 __ Str(temp_0, dst);
4396 __ Str(temp_1, src);
4397 }
4398 return;
4399 }
4400 default:
4401 UNREACHABLE();
4402 }
